headline: Billionaire Warren Buffett Owns 45 Stocks and ETFs. But Only One Has a Beefy 5% Dividend Yield.
summary: Billionaire Warren Buffett has always had a thing for companies that return capital to their shareholders.  Passive income can compound into vast sums of wealth and make money productive as investors wait for a stock to appreciate.  Buffett's company Berkshire Hathaway owns several high-yielding stocks in its portfolio.
